located near the town of Mit Rahina, 20 km (12 mi) south of Cairo.

Menes. Capital of Egypt during the Old Kingdom, The carved symbols are the 
gods of that time in Egypt

much of Egyptian history. Memphis is located south of the Nile River delta, 
on the west bank of the river, and about 15 miles (24 km) south of modern 
Cairo. Closely associated with the ancient city’s site are the cemeteries, 
or necropolises, of Memphis, where the famous pyramids of Egypt are 
located. From north to south the main pyramid fields are: Abū Ruwaysh, 
Giza, Zāwiyat al-ʿAryān, Abū Ṣīr, Ṣaqqārah, and Dahshūr. The Memphis 
archaeological zone was designated a UNESCO World Heritage site in 1979.﻿
